    "created_at": "2017-10-23T00:20:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-10-23T00:20:02Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I had a similar problem. I ran `npm i -g truffle` and then when I tried to run `truffle init` I got an error: `zsh: command not found: truffle`.  What solved it for me is to create a local `node_modules` with truffle installed in it, and then run that copy.\r\n\r\n1. run `npm init` and make a new npm project\r\n2. run `npm i truffle`\r\n3. run `./node_modules/.bin/truffle init` and it should work!",
